Latest on Red Age: Concentrations decrease in Pinellas, Manatee, and Sarasota
The latest report from the Florida Fish and Wildlife Commission shows a general decline in Redness concentrations for parts of the Tampa Bay area.
According to the FWC, sparse flowering conditions in the areas of Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte, and Collier cities are reported - which represent reduced concentrations.
In full bloom, the Red Age stretches some 130 miles along the coastline from northern Pinellas to southern Lee cities.
Colle can be found about 10 miles off the coast of Hillsborough City, but at fewer locations compared to last week.
Rooigety was also noticed in Pasco City.
Medium concentrations in or near the coast of Pinellas City have been reported in the past week, low to high concentrations near the coast of Hillsborough City, background to high concentrations in Manatee City, background to high concentrations in or near the coast of Sarasota City, background to medium concentrations in Charlotte City, background to high concentrations in or near the coast of Lee City, and low concentrations in Collier City.
Respiratory irritation continues to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee, and Collier cities.
Respiratory irritation has not been reported in North West Florida in the past week.
